<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>Deferred Shading</h3><p>Geometry pass writes material data to G-buffer (albedo, normal, roughness, depth). Lighting pass reads G-buffer — decouples light count from geometry complexity.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>PBR / Cook-Torrance</h3><p>Physically-based BRDF. Microfacet model: GGX distribution, Smith geometry function, Fresnel-Schlick approximation. Energy-conserving, artistically predictable.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Lumen (UE5)</h3><p>Software and hardware ray-traced global illumination. Radiance cache for diffuse GI. Screen space for short-range reflections. Lumen proxy meshes for SDF tracing.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>SSAO / GTAO</h3><p>Screen Space Ambient Occlusion darkens corners and crevices. Ground Truth AO (UE5) uses temporal accumulation for higher quality at similar cost.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
<div class="divider"></div>
<!-- SECTION 6: RENDER ENGINES -->
<section class="hidden" id="engines">
<h2>// Render Engines</h2>
<p>Real-time render engines embed decades of rendering research into accessible pipelines. The gap between real-time and offline rendering has nearly closed — UE5 Nanite + Lumen at 60fps produces imagery indistinguishable from path-traced renders to most viewers.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
