<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>SDF Rendering</h3><p>Signed Distance Fields represent geometry as distance functions. Ray marching through SDF enables complex implicit surfaces with zero triangles. Used in Unreal Nanite, font rendering, and AO.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Compute Shaders</h3><p>General-purpose GPU computation. Particle systems, fluid simulation, physics, and procedural mesh generation all happen on GPU via compute passes.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Noise Functions</h3><p>Perlin, Simplex, Worley, FBM. Basis for terrain, clouds, organic textures. GPU-optimized implementations run millions of noise samples per frame.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Mesh Shaders</h3><p>DX12 Ultimate / Vulkan feature replacing vertex + geometry shaders. Amplification shader culls meshlets; mesh shader generates geometry. Powers Nanite.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
